---
import ThreeColLayout from "src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

import AgentInstructions from "@components/AgentInstructions.svelte";
import AgentPersonas from "@components/AgentPersonas.svelte";
---

<ThreeColLayout title="TWONy-micro - Agents Settings">
  <h2 class="pageheading">Agents Settings</h2>
  <p class="pagesubline">
    Configure the virtual participants in your social media simulation. Each
    <strong>agent represents a different type of social media user</strong> with
    unique perspectives and communication styles. You can modify their personalities
    and instructions to see how different combinations of voices affect the overall
    conversation.
  </p>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h3 class="sectionheading">Customize Instructions</h3>
  <p class="sectionsubline">
    These are the <strong
      >basic rules that guide how all agents create posts and replies.</strong
    > Think of them as the general conversation guidelines - like telling everyone
    at a party what topics to discuss. Changes here affect every agent's behavior
    equally
  </p>

  <hr class="divider small" />

  <AgentInstructions client:load />

  <hr class="divider" />

  <h3 class="sectionheading">Customize Personas</h3>
  <p class="sectionsubline">
    Each persona is a <strong
      >unique virtual participant with their own personality, interests, and
      communication style.</strong
    > You can edit existing personas to change how they express themselves, add new
    ones to diversify the conversation, or remove personas to simplify the simulation.
    The icon and name help you identify who's speaking in the feed.
    <br /><br />
    Persona profiles originate from the <strong>Nemotron-Personas-USA</strong>
    dataset, an open-source dataset released under <strong>CC BY 4.0</strong>.
    It contains synthetically generated personas grounded in real-world demographic,
    geographic, and personality trait distributions to reflect population diversity.
    It is aligned with statistics for names, sex, age, background, marital status,
    education, occupation, location, and related attributes.
    <br /><br />
    The current release is focused on the United States and provides high-quality
    personas for a variety of modeling use cases. Source:
    <a
      href="https://huggingface.co/datasets/nvidia/Nemotron-Personas-USA"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noreferrer"
      class="underline"
      >Nemotron-Personas-USA on Hugging Face</a
    >.
    <br /><br />
    Emojis and usernames shown for personas are generated by <strong>GPT 5.2</strong>.
  </p>

  <hr class="divider small" />

  <AgentPersonas client:load />
</ThreeColLayout>
